OVERVIEW
--------
This log records held-out evaluation of the BASELINE (dumb) agent.
The baseline agent visits all dossier URLs then immediately files
a verdict of TRUE with 0.5 confidence — no citation tracing,
no synthetic detection, no case file updates.

These seeds were NEVER used during training (training used random
seeds from 0–99999, but we reserve 500–519 as our held-out eval set).

PURPOSE: establish 'before training' baseline numbers so we can
compare against the trained P2 model (PriyanshuHF/dead-internet-detective-model-p2).

SEED RANGES
-----------
  Training seeds : random draw from 0 – 99999 (per rollout, untracked)
  Held-out seeds : 500 – 519 (this evaluation, never touched in training)
  Difficulties   : easy, medium, hard
  Total episodes : 60  (20 seeds × 3 difficulties)

WHAT EACH SEED PRODUCES
-----------------------
Each seed deterministically generates a unique 'synthetic internet':
  easy  → 1 credible source + 2 synthetic (SEO farm + wellness blog)
  medium→ 1-2 credible sources + 3 synthetic pages
  hard  → 1 credible + 2 sophisticated fakes + SEO farm + wellness blog

Same seed + same difficulty = identical episode every time (deterministic).
Ground truth verdict is one of: true / false / unverifiable

RESULTS SUMMARY
---------------
  Difficulty Episodes   Mean Reward    Min      Max      Baseline Acc
  ---------- --------   -----------    -----    -----    ------------
  easy       20         0.38           0.305    0.455    0.5
  medium     20         0.3592         0.3067   0.4567   0.35
  hard       20         0.3825         0.3075   0.4575   0.5

  Overall mean reward (all 60 episodes): 0.3739

WHAT REWARD MEANS
-----------------
Terminal reward formula (on filing final report):
  0.30 × verdict_accuracy       (did agent get right answer?)
  0.25 × evidence_chain_quality  (did agent visit+cite real URLs?)
  0.20 × synthetic_detection     (did agent flag fake pages?)
  0.15 × internal_consistency    (did reasoning address contradictions?)
  0.10 × step_efficiency         (did agent avoid wasting steps?)
  All multiplied by 0.5, clamped to [-0.5, 1.0]
  Step exhaustion penalty: -0.15 if all steps used up

Baseline agent score breakdown (why it scores ~0.38):
  - Visits all dossier URLs → evidence_chain_quality = partial credit
  - Always files 'true' → verdict_accuracy depends on ground truth
    (40% of episodes have gt=true → gets credit those times)
  - Never detects synthetic sources → synthetic_detection = 0
  - No contradictions addressed → internal_consistency = 1.0 (no log)
  - Uses only 4 steps out of 40-80 → step_efficiency = high

COMPARISON: BASELINE vs TRAINED
--------------------------------
  Phase 1 model (AryanJain7031, easy only, 15 steps):
    Final training reward: ~0.010 (plateaued — easy curriculum too narrow)

  Phase 2 model (PriyanshuHF, easy+medium+hard, 20 steps):
    Final training reward: ~0.020–0.050 (peak seen: 0.293 on medium)
    Model repo: PriyanshuHF/dead-internet-detective-model-p2

  Baseline dumb agent (this eval, seeds 500-519):
    easy mean:   0.38
    medium mean: 0.3592
    hard mean:   0.3825

  Note: baseline scores ~0.38 because it accidentally benefits from
  step_efficiency (only uses 4 steps) and internal_consistency bonus
  (no contradictions logged = perfect consistency score).
  A trained agent will score higher by correctly detecting synthetic
  sources and filing the right verdict more often.

